Sixty-ninth
Legislative Assembly SENATE CONCURRENT RESOLUTION NO. 4013
of North Dakota
Introduced by
Senators Sickler, Erbele, Klein, Meyer
Representative Bahl
1 A concurrent resolution to support the electoral college, denounce the National Popular Vote
2 Interstate Compact, and invite interested states to form the Electoral College Interstate
3 Compact.
4 WHEREAS, the electoral college system respects states as the essential units in our
5 federal republic, protecting states' power and voice in presidential elections; and
6 WHEREAS, the electoral college system creates an appropriate balance between rural and
7 urban interests and ensures the winning candidate has support from multiple regions of the
8 country; and
9 WHEREAS, the electoral college system ensures each state's electoral votes are awarded
10 based on how the state's citizens vote; and
11 WHEREAS, the nation's founders' rejected a national popular vote for president and instead
12 created the Electoral College; and
13 WHEREAS, the National Popular Vote Interstate Compact diminishes the importance of
14 individual states in presidential elections, creates the potential for nationwide recounts, and
15 opens the door to greater federal control of elections; and
16 WHEREAS, the constitutionality of the National Popular Vote Interstate Compact is doubtful
17 because it appears to violate the Compact Clause of the United States Constitution and the
18 intent of the electoral college clauses;
19 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF NORTH DAKOTA, THE
20 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING THEREIN:
21 That the Sixty-ninth Legislative Assembly supports the Electoral College and believes the
22 National Popular Vote Interstate Compact may be unconstitutional; and
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, in response to the creation of the National Popular Vote
24 Interstate Compact, North Dakota and all other interested states should consider forming an
25 Electoral College Interstate Compact, which would prohibit requiring state electors to cast
